# Dependency Injection Guidelines

Always use constructor injection for dependencies. Depend on abstractions, not concrete implementations. Use service locators (like GetIt) for dependency registration. Test with mocks.

**Key principles:**
- Constructor injection only
- Depend on abstract classes
- No global singletons
- Register in central location
- Keep dependencies mockable

**Example:**
```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
class AuthBloc {
  final AuthProvider _authProvider;
  AuthBloc({required AuthProvider authProvider})
      : _authProvider = authProvider;
}

// ❌ WRONG
class AuthBloc {
  final _authProvider = FirebaseAuthProvider(); // Hard-coded!
}
```
